-- Positive EPS Surprises for First Quarter of ’13 for S&P 500
-- B y   W e n d y   S o o n g
-- 2013-06-12T20:37:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-12/positive-eps-surprises-for-first-quarter-of-13-for-s-p-500.html
Following are positive and unchanged
earnings surprises for the first quarter of 2013 for companies in the
 Standard & Poor’s (SPX)  500 Index. So far, 66.7 percent (331 out of 496) of the
 S&P 500  have reported positive surprises, and 9.1 percent (45 out of 496)
have reported zero percent surprises.  The median for positive earnings surprises is 7.6 percent and the
fourth-spread average is 8.2 percent. A fourth-spread average is the
average unaffected by observations in the smallest 25 percent or the
largest 25 percent of the data.  This list ranks percent surprises of  actual earnings  to earnings
estimates for the quarter. Profit figures are based on income from
continuing operations excluding some gains and losses.  Earnings estimates 
are provided by Bloomberg.  
